TY  - JOUR
AU  - Mueller, Elisabeth
T1  - Returns to Private Equity - Idiosyncratic Risk Does Matter!*
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfq003
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 15
IS  - 3
SP  - 545
EP  - 574
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Owners of private companies often invest a substantial share of their net worth in one company, which exposes them to idiosyncratic risk. We investigate whether owners of US companies require compensation for lack of diversification in the form of higher returns on equity. Exposure to idiosyncratic risk is measured as the share of the owner’s net worth invested in the company. Equity returns are measured as the earnings rate and as capital gains. For both returns measures we find a positive and significant influence of exposure to idiosyncratic risk. This paper improves our understanding of returns on private equity.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfq003
ER  - 



